# SQL Injection (SQLi)

> Injection attack where malicious SQL queries are inserted into input fields to manipulate the database.

---

## 🔍 Types of SQLi

### 1. In-Band SQLi
- **Error-Based** — Uses DB error messages to extract data
- **Union-Based** — Uses UNION to combine results

### 2. Blind SQLi
- **Boolean-Based** — True/False responses
- **Time-Based** — Uses SLEEP/WAITFOR delays

### 3. Out-of-Band SQLi
- Uses DNS/HTTP channels to exfiltrate data
- Used when in-band not possible

